<% content_for :title, "MCP server · Sessy" %>

<div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-6 sm:px-6">
  <h1 class="text-lg font-semibold">MCP server</h1>
  <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 max-w-2xl">
    Connect AI agents like Claude Code, Cursor, and Codex to this Sessy instance over the
    Model Context Protocol. Agents can search email events, inspect message timelines with
    bounce diagnostics, and pull delivery stats &mdash; read-only.
  </p>

  <div class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-medium">Endpoint</h2>
        <pre class="mt-2 border border-zinc-950/10 dark:border-white/10 px-3 py-2 text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code class="select-all"><%= mcp_endpoint_url %></code></pre>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">
          Authentication uses an API key as a bearer token.
          <%= link_to "Create one here", api_keys_path, class: "underline hover:text-zinc-900 dark:hover:text-zinc-100" %>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-medium">Claude Code</h2>
        <pre class="mt-2 border border-zinc-950/10 dark:border-white/10 px-3 py-2 text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>claude mcp add --transport http sessy <%= mcp_endpoint_url %> \
  --header "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY"</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-medium">Cursor</h2>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">Add to <code>~/.cursor/mcp.json</code>:</p>
        <pre class="mt-2 border border-zinc-950/10 dark:border-white/10 px-3 py-2 text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>{
  "mcpServers": {
    "sessy": {
      "url": "<%= mcp_endpoint_url %>",
      "headers": { "Authorization": "Bearer YOUR_API_KEY" }
    }
  }
}</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-medium">Codex</h2>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">Add to <code>~/.codex/config.toml</code> (with <code>SESSY_API_KEY</code> exported in your shell):</p>
        <pre class="mt-2 border border-zinc-950/10 dark:border-white/10 px-3 py-2 text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>[mcp_servers.sessy]
url = "<%= mcp_endpoint_url %>"
bearer_token_env_var = "SESSY_API_KEY"</code></pre>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400 dark:text-zinc-500">
        ChatGPT custom connectors require OAuth, which Sessy doesn't support yet &mdash; planned for a future release.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-medium">Tools</h2>
        <table class="mt-2 min-w-full text-sm">
          <tbody>
            <% @tools.each do |tool| %>
              <tr class="border-b border-zinc-950/5 dark:border-white/5 align-top">
                <td class="py-2.5 pr-3 whitespace-nowrap"><code class="font-medium"><%= tool.name_value %></code></td>
                <td class="py-2.5 text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400"><%= tool.description_value %></td>
              </tr>
            <% end %>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="text-sm text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 space-y-4">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-medium text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">Running behind Cloudflare or a CDN?</h3>
          <p class="mt-1">Bot protection (like Cloudflare's managed challenge) blocks MCP clients &mdash; they can't solve challenges. Add a WAF rule that skips bot protection for the <code>/mcp</code> path, or requests from your agents will silently fail.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-medium text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">Security notes</h3>
          <p class="mt-1">API keys grant read access to all of this account's email data; keys live in your editor's config files, so treat them like passwords and revoke unused ones. Enabling HTTP Basic auth later does <em>not</em> revoke keys minted earlier &mdash; review the <%= link_to "API keys page", api_keys_path, class: "underline hover:text-zinc-900 dark:hover:text-zinc-100" %> after locking down an install.</p>
          <p class="mt-1">Email subjects, recipient addresses, and bounce diagnostics are third-party content. The server instructs agents to treat them as data, never as instructions, and tools are read-only by design.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
